Author-Name: Paul D. Ellis 
Title: Social Structure and Intermediation: Market-making Strategies in International Exchange 
Abstract:
 Information gaps between markets create opportunities for international
 trade intermediaries to negotiate cross-border exchanges. Faced with the
 prospect of eventually being eliminated from these exchanges,
 intermediaries must continually search for new opportunities to mediate
 international exchange. In this paper an original explanation is derived
 from the core principles of structural hole theory to explain how these
 market-making firms operate in the tension found between the inevitable
 decay of existing exchange relationships and the uncertainty of finding
 replacement sources of income. Copyright 2003 Blackwell Publishing Ltd.. 
