Title: AFTER THE INK DRIES: THE INTERACTION OF TRUST AND CONTROL IN US-BASED INTERNATIONAL JOINT VENTURES 
Abstract:
 This study empirically examines the moderating effects of age and partner
 trust on the relationship between control mechanisms and perceptions of
 performance in 129 US-based international joint ventures (IJVs). A
 reliance on formal control mechanisms and general managers' perceptions of
 IJV performance were found to be positively related in younger IJVs, but
 this relationship became negative in more mature IJVs. In addition, social
 control mechanisms and perceptions of IJV performance were positively
 related, but only in the presence of affect-based trust between the
 parents. Copyright 2002 Blackwell Publishers Ltd.. 
