Title: Strategists and Strategy-making: Strategic Exchange and the Shaping of Individual Lives and Organizational Futures 
Abstract:
 A "strategic exchange" framework for the analysis of the relationship
 between the personal strategies of strategists and the strategic direction
 followed by organizations is presented. The exchange relationship that
 strategists have with their organization and the exchange relationship
 between the organization and the constituencies upon which it is resource
 dependent is examined and some of the processes and practices that this
 can entail are illustrated with the case of Strath Guitars. The case study
 also illustrates the value of "ethnographic fiction science" as an
 innovative type of research account which is especially appropriate for
 the reporting of studies of the detailed interpersonal and social
 processes associated with organizational strategy-making. Copyright Blackwell Publishing Ltd 2003. 
