Title: Building Better Theory by Bridging the Quantitative-Qualitative Divide 
Abstract:
  Qualitative methods for data collection and analysis are not mystical,
 but they are powerful, particularly when used to build new or refine
 existing theories. This article provides an introduction to qualitative
 methods and an overview of tactics for ensuring rigor in qualitative
 research useful for the novice researcher, as well as more experienced
 researchers interested in expanding their methodological repertoire or
 seeking guidance on how to evaluate qualitative research. We focus our
 discussion on the qualitative analytical technique of grounded theory
 building, and suggest that organizational research has much to gain by
 coupling of use of qualitative and quantitative research methods. Copyright Blackwell Publishing Ltd 2006. 
