Title: Two Dimensions of the Internationalization of Firms 
Abstract:
 The paper argues that there are two dimensions of internationalization:
 one which refers to the production activities of firms abroad and one
 which focuses on the corporate governance dimension of firms. While the
 first one is well known in the literature on internationalization, the
 financial dimension has not yet been addressed empirically. At the same
 time there are indicators that financial internationalization is gaining
 importance. Using a sample of the 100 largest German companies it shows
 that both dimensions, the real and the financial dimension, do not co-vary
 and therefore cannot be combined into one index. Copyright (c) Blackwell Publishing Ltd 2003.. 
