Title: Reflecting on Reflexivity: Reflexive Textual Practices in Organization and Management Theory 
Abstract:
 This paper identifies four sets of textual practices that researchers in
 the field of organization and management theory (OMT) have used in their
 attempts to be reflexive. We characterize them as multi-perspective,
 multi-voicing, positioning and destabilizing. We show how each set of
 practices can help to produce reflexive research, but also how each
 embodies limitations and paradoxes. Finally, we consider the interplay
 among these sets of practices to develop ideas for new avenues for
 reflexive practice by OMT researchers. Copyright (c) Blackwell Publishing Ltd 2008. 
