 pressure from imports and foreign direct investment. We show this was the
 case for 407 US firms between 1987 and 2003. Results for a panel of 95
 German firms reveal a similar reaction to pressure from an increase in
 imports, but show no reaction to increased exposure to incoming foreign
 direct investment during the same time frame. Copyright (c) Blackwell Publishing Ltd 2008. 
