Title: Resourceful Sensemaking in an Administrative Group 
Abstract:
 In this study, we present the concept of resourceful sensemaking as an
 extension of Weick's sensemaking theory. Resourceful sensemaking extends
 Weick's theory by carefully examining the influence of the lifeworld on
 organizational sensemaking practices. Lifeworld factors that affect
 organizational sensemaking are brought out in a dialectical method wherein
 a working definition of the resourceful sensemaking concept is compared
 with the sensemaking practices of an administrative group. We then show
 how this dialectical method can help develop a more robust formulation of
 the resourceful sensemaking concept. The paper ends by discussing the
 strengths and shortcomings of the concept and suggesting directions for
 future organizational sensemaking research. Copyright Blackwell Publishing Ltd 2004. 
