Title: On the Review Process and Journal Development 
Abstract:
 This paper describes the editorial and review process currently operating
 at "JMS" and offers the Editors' perspective on the journal's growth over
 the past three years. We first outline what we think is the essence of a
 "JMS" article. Then, we describe the review process from the editor's
 initial decision, to the reviewers' comments, to the editor's final
 editorial decisions, and including the process of accepting a paper. We
 suggest four main reasons for rejecting a paper: lack of contribution,
 failure to develop a theoretical contribution, fatal flaws in methods and
 deficiencies in analysis. With respect to the journal's progress, we show
 that "JMS" has significantly increased its position in the ISI rankings to
 19th and its impact factor to 1.180. In addition, the journal experienced
 a 222 per cent increase in submissions from 2003 to 2005. Copyright Blackwell Publishing Ltd 2006. 
