Title: Organizational Learning in Multinationals: R&D Networks of Japanese and US MNEs in the UK 
Abstract:
 The institutional approach treats organizational forms and behaviour as
 contingent upon institutions that are durable and socially embedded and so
 several authors have argued that the nature and modes of operation of
 multinational enterprises (MNEs) vary according to their national origins.
 This paper examines the ways in which national patterns of organization
 and innovation affect Japanese and US MNEs' global R&D networks and
 transnational learning, based on case studies of their R&D laboratories in
 the UK. In particular, it focuses on how these MNEs tap into foreign
 academic knowledge base and scientific labour through collaborative links
 with higher education institutions. Copyright (c) Blackwell Publishing Ltd 2003. 
