Title: Dimensions of Social Capital and Firm Competitiveness Improvement: The Mediating Role of Information Sharing 
Abstract:
 This study investigates the mediating role of information sharing in the
 relationships between dimensions of social capital and firm
 competitiveness, thereby positing a possible explanation for the divergent
 empirical results of the social capital-performance relationship in the
 existing literature. The study uses a sample of 108 Hong Kong-based
 Chinese family-owned firms from the manufacturing sector. Largely
 supporting the theoretical predictions, the results from multiple
 regression and structural equation model tests show that information
 sharing plays a mediating role in the relationships between three
 dimensions of social capital (trust, network ties, and repeated
 transactions) and firm competitiveness improvement. Copyright Blackwell Publishing Ltd 2007. 
