Author-Name: José de Jesus Salazar 
Title: Taking Friedman Seriously: Maximizing Profits and Social Performance 
Abstract:
 This paper examines the situation of firms that have two objectives:
 profit maximization and social performance. By looking comparatively at
 the cases of altruism, coerced egoism, and strategy, this paper uses the
 tools of microeconomics to define the optimal level of social output that
 should be produced in each case. We show that it is wiser for the firm to
 act strategically than to be coerced into making investments in corporate
 social responsibility. In addition, we argue that greater overall social
 output will be achieved by the strategic approach, than by the altruistic
 approach. Copyright Blackwell Publishing Ltd 2006. 
