Title: A Prescriptive Analysis of Search and Discovery 
Abstract:
 I develop a prescriptive model of entrepreneurial search and discovery,
 which operationalizes constrained, systematic search. This approach
 appears to be superior to the alertness perspective in both the number and
 the wealth-creating potential of the opportunities that it can assist
 entrepreneurs to discover. Essentially, this research shows how
 entrepreneurs can improve their search effectiveness by systematically
 restricting their searching to known domains, which I elaborate
 prescriptively. Finally, I discuss the implications of the approach for
 researchers, educators and entrepreneurs. Copyright Blackwell Publishing Ltd 2007. 
