Author-Name: Michael H. Lubatkin 
Author-Name: William S. Schulze 
Title: Crossing the Threshold from Founder Management to Professional Management: A Governance Perspective 
Abstract:
 We argue that the challenges faced by threshold firms are deeply rooted in
 governance characteristics (i.e. the incentives, authority and legitimacy)
 which imbue them with characteristic capabilities, disabilities and path
 dependencies. Whereas Zahra and Filatotchev (2004) reason the principal
 problem facing threshold firms relates to organizational learning and
 knowledge management, we posit resource acquisition and utilization to be
 equally important. Moreover, we argue governance theory is more able than
 a knowledge-based perspective to explain the "root causes" of the learning
 and resource issues faced by threshold firms as well as the complex set of
 processes involved in their effective management. Copyright Blackwell Publishing Ltd 2004. 
