Title: Firms as Realizations of Entrepreneurial Visions 
Abstract:
 In the debate on why firms exist, the question of who chooses between
 firms and markets and on what basis is rarely addressed. This paper argues
 that the choice is a core element of the entrepreneurial pursuit of
 visions or conceptions of business opportunities. To successfully organize
 resources into the envisioned businesses - be it via firms or markets -
 resource owners must be coordinated on the entrepreneur's conception of
 the business and be motivated to perform properly. To solve the dual
 problem, the organizational form of the firm offers the entrepreneur
 unique advantages not feasible under the organizational form of markets. Copyright Blackwell Publishing Ltd 2007. 
