 intellectual capital, and its three knowledge components - human,
 organizational, and social capital. We hypothesize that the impact of each
 component on financial performance is contingent upon the values of the
 other components, and that these leveraging effects are themselves
 contingent upon the industry conditions in which a business operates. Our
 hypotheses are supported using line-of-business survey and FDIC data
 (within-industry/within-geographic region) from two non-competing resource
 niches of the banking industry (personal and commercial banking). Copyright Blackwell Publishing Ltd 2006. 
