 performance of joint-ventures. We first study the relationship and
 predictions of two relevant theories, i.e., the theory about cultural
 diversity and that about cultural distance. After that, we apply the
 theories to study the behaviour and performance of Sino-Japanese and
 Sino-West joint ventures (JVs). Processing data from 2718 such JVs in
 different parts of China, we show evidence supporting our arguments. Our
 paper concludes with a discussion on the implications of the findings. Copyright 2002 Blackwell Publishers Ltd.. 
